title: For Sale:  Brand New Smith & Wesson M&P40 M2.0
postcontent: PLEASE DON'T EMAIL ASKING IF I STILL HAVE THIS, WHEN THE GUN IS GONE THE AD WILL BE GONE TOO.I recently ordered a Smith & Wesson M&P40 M2.0 and decided that, despite the serious upgrades S&W made, I'm not sure I want to keep. First the good, the trigger is a huge improvement with a distinct, shorter tactile reset and much smoother pull. Also, the frame has a stainless steel chassis to reduce the already negligible flex. Additionally, there are now 4 interchangable backstraps instead of just 3, the new one being a medium/large. The tool used for disassembly and that holds the backstrap in place is also much easier to remove and replace. Now the one update I'm not sure I care for, the factory stipple job, man this thing is grippy and I prefer to have great checkering or stippling on the front and backstraps but little to none on the sides so I can change my grip if needed. Your mileage may vary.Additionally, I bought a set of Trijicon Night Sights that I haven't yet installed and an El Paso Saddlery holster. I paid $150 for the Trijicons and $95 for the holster and these items are available for sale.I expect my full asking price (exactly what I paid) for this brand new firearm and accessories, it might be the first M&P40 M2.0 in Abq. Again, this is a brand new firearm, zero rounds fired outside the factory!
